    bf:summary [ a bf:Summary ;
            rdfs:label "\"To fight this war, ten million people must go to work by the end of 1943. Today the problem of manpower is crucial in our factories and our farms. This film presents the problems and confusion now existing. Paul V. McNutt, Chairman of the War Manpower Commission, introduces the problems and suggests voluntary steps to be followed by employers and workers, cooperating with Government agencies, in attacking the problem\"--A list of U.S. war information films, p. 14."@en ] ;
